<TEXT>
silvana mangano the italian actress whose 
role as a sensual country girl in bitter rice made her a star 
died today in a madrid hospital after several days in a coma a 
hospital spokeswoman said she was 59 
ms mangano went into the coma after she suffered a heart attack 
during surgery for cancer said the luz clinic spokeswoman on 
condition of anonymity the actress had been suffering from cancer 
for several years 
film director pier paolo pasolini once called her a bitter 
beauty who shined like a pearl but was always distant in 
later years her career was overshadowed by that of her husband of 
34 years movie producer dino de laurentiis 
she was born in rome on april 21 1930 the daughter of a 
sicilian railroad worker and an english mother 
the trained dancer model and former miss rome played only bit 
parts until she landed the starring role in director giuseppe de 
santis 1949 film bitter rice considered one of best examples 
of the postwar italian neorealism movement 
filmgoers worldwide turned out to see the voluptuous actress 
cavorting in the fields of the po valley wearing a tight sweater 
shorts and thighhigh black stockings 
she then starred in movies for such directors as vittorio de 
sica pasolini mario monicelli and luchino visconti 
although ms manganos fame was overshadowed by two other 
haunting beauties of the italian screen sophia loren and gina 
lollobrigida she beat out the latter in auditions for bitter 
rice 
while she achieved stardom ms mangano never seemed comfortable 
in the role or even in making movies 
i agreed to appear in bitter rice more because i needed 
money than out of the desire to have a film career she once told 
an interviewer 
the actress once said i never liked myself neither when i 
was a roundish girl nor when i became a slender woman 
after a long absence from the screen she had a small role in 
the 1984 film dune and appeared in the 1986 film dark eyes 
alongside marcello mastroianni whom she described as her first 
love 
we used to live in the same part of rome when we were kids we 
were in love i was 16 and he was 22 
as to her infrequent movie roles she explained at the time 
the truth is that making films is not my passion and i thought 
it was better for me not to work 
she separated from de laurentiis in 1983 and filed for divorce 
last year the couple had three daughters and a son who died in an 
air crash in alaska in 1981 
she spent the last few years living in in madrid with francesca 
her youngest daughter who is married to a spanish film producer 
the hospital spokeswoman gave no information regarding funeral 
or memorial services 
the spanish national news agency efe quoted sources close to the 
family as saying ms manganos body would be cremated sunday and 
the remains sent to an unidentified new york cemetery to be placed 
next to those of her son 
