searched the mans home and emerged with boxes of possible evidence 
and were checking blood stains found in his vehicle 
if people hear that theyll quit looking for her ms 
brannen said 
police and hundreds of volunteers have conducted numerous 
searches of the area but they have curtailed those until they get 
new leads proffitt said 
despite the areas middleclass residential nature about 30 
miles south of washington dc fairfax county has had its share 
of trouble in addition to the rosie gordon slaying a thirdgrader 
was raped last year in an elementary school restroom 
that incident prompted the fairfax county public schools to 
institute a comprehensive childsafety program for the children and 
staff said assistant superintendent dolores bohen crisis 
counseling teams are routinely sent into schools when needed she 
said 
there are no solid numbers on how many missing children there 
are as these cases are not always reported and there is no central 
clearinghouse for the information 
scott mandel on loan from the corpus cristi texas sheriffs 
office to the center for missing and exploited children estimated 
that at any point 1 million to 15 million children are missing 
of whom the majority are runaways or socalled throwaways children 
kicked out by their parents most return the same day he said 
the next largest number are parental abduction cases involving 
50000 to 300000 children he said 
police confirmed that melissas father michael brannen a toy 
store manager in garland texas who has not seen the girl in two 
years was in texas when she disappeared police dont think her 
disappearance is part of a domestic dispute 
as for abductions by strangers he said the center had heard of 
511 cases during its first five years of operation ending sept 30 
of those 158 children had been returned alive 112 were located 
dead the rest are still missing 
ms brannen a single parent who was working as an accountant 
for a defense contractor and parttime for two jewelry stores 
rarely sleeps these days shes never alone family and friends 
answer the phone 
she castigates herself for not being more cautious about melissa 
although she estimates it took only two minutes at most for melissa 
to vanish 
you can say lots of i should have dones she says i 
