gov rose mofford says she agrees with the state 
attorney generals assessment and will tell the state parole board 
that her commutations of two murder sentences are void 
attorney general bob corbins opinion friday said the 
commutations of james hamm and carl kummerlowe could be considered 
void because the parole board that recommended them earlier in the 
year did not fully comply with a victimnotification law 
the attorney generals opinion confirms my original belief 
that these commutations were flawed and must be considered void 
mofford said in a statement 
hamm and his wife prisonerrights activist donna leone hamm 
would not comment on the ruling kummerlowe has refused to comment 
