<TEXT>
irans divided military forces saturday 
completed their most extensive maneuvers in the persian gulf in a 
decade and proved they could work together tehran radio reported 
the broadcast monitored in nicosia quoted navy commander rear 
adm ali shamkhani as saying that some good and amazing results 
were gained in the maneuvers 
he said the exercise demonstrated that the regular armed forces 
could effectively coordinate with the revolutionary guards to repel 
any threat the radio reported 
the 350000strong revolutionary guards were formed during the 
1979 islamic revolution as an ideologically reliable force to 
counter an army trained under the late shah mohammad reza pahlavi 
but the regular navy army and air force were constantly at odds 
with the revolutionary guards during the eightyear iraniraq war 
which has been halted by a ceasefire since august 1988 
both forces have opposed efforts to merge them but president 
hashemi rafsanjani has combined the defense and guards ministries 
to streamline the chain of command and improve coordination 
the iranian air force and regular army also participated in the 
maneuvers which covered 7500 square miles of the gulf and the 
adjacent gulf of oman the radio said 
it said that more than 10000 men took part and that tens of 
navy destroyers missile craft troop carriers hovercraft jet 
fighters minedetecting helicopters and revolutionary guards 
vessels were involved in carrying out complex electronic warfare 
operations and amphibious landings 
tehran television also monitored in nicosia showed a number of 
patrol boats destroyers hovercraft and landing craft in the gulf 
on friday 
the radio said the revolutionary guards who have their own air 
and naval wings used for the first time two new types of 
iranianbuilt speedboats armed with small multiple rocket 
launchers 
the vessels classed as imam1 and imam2 were constructed by 
the revolutionary guards defense factories the report said 
rafsanjani said last month that his navy had acquired vital 
equipment that would enhance its capability 
he did not elaborate but western military analysts believe iran 
may have deployed chinesemade silkworm missiles on its ships none 
of the vessels shown in the television broadcast appeared to be 
armed with silkworms 
the analysts said irans navy is short of usmade shiptoship 
harpoon missiles and has been seeking a new seaborne system 
iran is believed to have testfired a shipborne silkworm 
missile in the gulf three months ago 
the 58000ton uss new jersey sailed through the strait of 
hormuz into the persian gulf just before the maneuvers began dec 9 
the battleship the biggest warship to sail into the gulf in 
recent times left the waterway tuesday for its regular station 
with a us naval task force in the arabian sea 
</TEXT>
