revolutionary reforms this year in eastern europe as a process 
characterized by political pluralism human dignity and human 
rights 
this is a historically unprecedented opportunity for our 
nations which can be realized only through cooperation and not by 
selfish national interest it said 
delegates represented polands solidarity labor movement the 
east german new forum the czechoslovak groups democratic 
initiative civic forum charter 77 glasnost against violence and 
the independent hungarian initiative representing the hungarian 
minority in slovakia and the hungarian democratic forum that acted 
