supervision of international observers 
french soldier of fortune bob denard and the other european 
mercenaries left the islands thursday and friday with some flying 
from moroni to paris and some to johannesburg south africa 
france the former colonial power sent 200 troops to the 
islands after djohar requested military assistance under a mutual 
defense treaty to restore the countrys security south africa is 
involved because it has a major financial interest in the islands 
off southeastern africa 
south african and french officials were reported to be trying to 
find a final destination for the mercenaries a spokesman for the 
