<TEXT>
a california endurance swimmer who has 
crossed the bering strait plans to risk the treacherous icy waters 
along the southernmost tip of south america next month 
lynne cox 32 of los alamitos plans to leave sunday for 
washington dc to to work out the final diplomatic details of 
her swim through the beagle channel a waterway along the 
longdisputed argentinachile border 100 miles north of cape horn 
the 5 to 15mile channel crossing marks ms coxs most 
ambitious swim the pacific and atlantic oceans collide in the 
narrow channel creating strong erratic currents and choppy waves 
water temperatures range from 38 degrees to 45 degrees 
scientists say that most people die of hypothermia after 20 minutes 
in 38degree water but ms cox plans to spend at least two hours 
in the water 
the swim is to take place between jan 11 and jan 25 depending 
on the weather wind and water currents 
this is going to be more difficult more cold more remote 
and more of a real challenge than anything i have ever done ms 
cox said in a telephone interview from her home friday 
she already has attracted international attention for dangerous 
endurance swims that would leave most other longdistance swimmers 
cold 
in 1987 she overcame superpower politics and the 39degree 
waters off western alaska to swim about five miles across the 
bering strait from little diomede island in the united states to 
big diomede island in the soviet union 
the unprecedented crossing drew warm praise from soviet leader 
mikhail s gorbachev who helped clear the way for ms cox 11mile 
swim in august 1988 across siberias lake baikal the worlds 
deepest lake 
both swims were intended to promote sovietamerican friendship 
the beagle channel swim is designed to symbolically bring 
together argentina and chile two countries that have fought over 
land around the channel for a century 
i like the idea of reaching beyond borders in many areas the 
idea of reaching beyond political borders and also the 
psychological borders she said 
the swim also is a test of her physical abilities 
i did the bering strait this is sort of to reach beyond that 
to see how much further you can go she said 
ms cox who is in prime distanceswimming form of 180 pounds on 
a 5foot6 frame also has crossed the english channel and the 
strait of magellan 
she plans to leave for buenos aires argentina on friday where 
she will stay until dec 27 from there she plans to travel to the 
argentine city of ushuaia where she will slowly acclimate herself 
to the channels frigid waters 
right now im going through all the emotions you normally go 
through in a day she said youre excited youre afraid 
youre uncertain youre hopeful all sorts of emotions 
but i do know that when i first go down there and put my toe 
in that cold water ill say my god what did i get into this 
time 
