hand grenade after being surrounded by police but an official 
coroners report said rodriguez gacha and the other men died from 
bullet wounds to the head and body 
rodriguez gacha was the second most important leader of the 
medellin cartel which together with a rival group from the 
southern city of cali is responsible for 80 percent of the cocaine 
sold on us streets 
the other cartel leaders are escobar and jorge luis ochoa 
rodriguez gacha was perhaps the most ruthless of the three 
authorities blamed the billionaire trafficker for hundreds of 
